<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="432" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1400,1426]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small sized (CW &lt;
<quantity box="[560,645,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
). Carapace subquadrate, flat, dorsal surface pitted (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1300,1400,1426]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov., dorsal habitus. (A) male holotype SYSBM002003; (B) female paratype SYSBM002007." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899750/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); epigastric cristae low; not confluent with postorbital cristae (
<figureCitation box="[726,787,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov., dorsal habitus. (A) male holotype SYSBM002003; (B) female paratype SYSBM002007." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899750/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig.1</figureCitation>
); external orbital angle bluntly triangular, almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[159,224,1472,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov., dorsal habitus. (A) male holotype SYSBM002003; (B) female paratype SYSBM002007." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899750/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Epistomial median lobe narrowly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[746,835,1472,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-132@5.[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–D) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (E–F) female paratype (16.4 × 13.0 mm), SYSBM002007; (A) Cephalothorax, anterior view; (B) anterior thoracic sternum; (C) anterior thoracic sternum and pleon, ventral view; (D) sterno-pleonal cavity with G1 in situ, ventral view. Female paratype (mm): (E) pleon, ventral view; (F) vulvae, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899752/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Maxilliped III with relatively broad ischium, exopod reaching beyond anterior edge of ischium, with long flagellum (
<figureCitation box="[875,966,1508,1534]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Cheliped palm surface relatively rugose (
<figureCitation box="[159,279,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 3F–G</figureCitation>
). Male anterior thoracic sternum wide, width 1.8 × length (
<figureCitation box="[928,1015,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-132@5.[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–D) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (E–F) female paratype (16.4 × 13.0 mm), SYSBM002007; (A) Cephalothorax, anterior view; (B) anterior thoracic sternum; (C) anterior thoracic sternum and pleon, ventral view; (D) sterno-pleonal cavity with G1 in situ, ventral view. Female paratype (mm): (E) pleon, ventral view; (F) vulvae, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899752/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Male pleon broadly triangular, tip of telson semicircular (
<figureCitation box="[380,469,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-132@5.[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–D) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (E–F) female paratype (16.4 × 13.0 mm), SYSBM002007; (A) Cephalothorax, anterior view; (B) anterior thoracic sternum; (C) anterior thoracic sternum and pleon, ventral view; (D) sterno-pleonal cavity with G1 in situ, ventral view. Female paratype (mm): (E) pleon, ventral view; (F) vulvae, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899752/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). G1 generally slender, pointing anterolaterally, terminal segment large and stout with wide opening at truncate tip, inner margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[730,907,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 3C–E, H–I</figureCitation>
). G2 with subquadrate basal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1423,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Female vulva ovate, large, located within sternite VI (
<figureCitation box="[754,840,1652,1678]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-132@5.[162,1426,453,1874]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–D) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (E–F) female paratype (16.4 × 13.0 mm), SYSBM002007; (A) Cephalothorax, anterior view; (B) anterior thoracic sternum; (C) anterior thoracic sternum and pleon, ventral view; (D) sterno-pleonal cavity with G1 in situ, ventral view. Female paratype (mm): (E) pleon, ventral view; (F) vulvae, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899752/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="432" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1688,1714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is an arbitrary combination of the zoogeographic location of the 
<typeStatus box="[1251,1299,1689,1715]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">type</typeStatus>
locality, the Jianghuai freshwater zoogeographic dominion (
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, C. &amp; Ebach, M. C. &amp; Ahyong, S. T." box="[685,904,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" pagination="271 - 298" refId="ref5148" refString="Huang, C. &amp; Ebach, M. C. &amp; Ahyong, S. T. (2020 a) Bioregionalisation of the freshwater zoogeographical areas of mainland China. Zootaxa, 4742 (2), 271 - 298. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4742.2.3" type="journal article" year="2020">
Huang 
<emphasis box="[769,825,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">et al.</emphasis>
2020a
</bibRefCitation>
), and the genus name, 
<taxonomicName authority="Savigny, 1816" authorityName="Savigny" authorityYear="1816" box="[1161,1432,1724,1750]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Potamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1161,1262,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Potamon</emphasis>
Savigny, 1816
</taxonomicName>
. Gender: neuter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="432" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1364,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Distribution.</emphasis>
Huo Shan county, Lu’an city, 
<collectingRegion box="[693,872,1796,1822]" country="China" name="Anhui" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Anhui province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[883,953,1796,1822]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">China</collectingCountry>
; Yingshan County, Huanggang City, 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Hubei Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[265,336,1832,1858]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="433" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1364,2039]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,825]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="433" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang, 2022" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,482,1868,1894]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Jianghuaimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,482,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Jianghuaimon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[489,594,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[489,594,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a rather unexceptional external appearance and most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Turkay &amp; Dai, 1997" authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,561,1904,1930]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Bottapotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Bottapotamon</emphasis>
Türkay &amp; Dai, 1997
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Turkay &amp; Dai, 1997" authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[625,1035,1904,1930]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Neilupotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,784,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Neilupotamon</emphasis>
Türkay &amp; Dai, 
<quantity box="[979,1035,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07238" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" unit="in" value="1997.0">1997</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in its small size (CW &lt;
<quantity box="[1337,1424,1904,1930]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
), relatively flat carapace with regions distinct, bluntly triangular external orbital angle and slightly unequal chelipeds. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang, 2022" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,311,1976,2002]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Jianghuaimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,311,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Jianghuaimon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[319,426,1976,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[319,426,1976,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Dai &amp; Ng, 1994" authorityName="Dai &amp; Ng" authorityYear="1994" box="[607,987,1976,2003]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Huananpotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,795,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="432">Huananpotamon</emphasis>
Dai &amp; Ng, 
<quantity box="[931,987,1976,2002]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06476" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" unit="in" value="1994.0">1994</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general external appearance to some extent, its relatively small size (CW &lt;
<quantity box="[604,690,2012,2038]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
), having stripe patterned ambulatory legs and a distinctive oval- shaped gold-colour pattern on the third maxilliped. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang, 2022" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[885,1045,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Jianghuaimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[885,1045,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Jianghuaimon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1057,1167,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1057,1167,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
markedly differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,310,187,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Bottapotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Bottapotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dai &amp; Ng" authorityYear="1994" box="[327,515,187,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Huananpotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,515,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Huananpotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[577,736,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Neilupotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[577,736,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Neilupotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its unique G1 structure, which is pointed anterolaterally, subterminal segment slightly curved inwards, terminal segment large and very stout, inner margin strongly convex, tip truncated with wide opening almost same width as terminal segment (
<figureCitation box="[990,1172,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 3C–E, H–I</figureCitation>
). In contrast, the G 
<quantity box="[1396,1436,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,310,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Bottapotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Bottapotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is pointed anteromedially, with the subterminal segment generally straight, terminal segment large and slender, inner margin concave, tip truncated with opening smaller than terminal segment width (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, N. &amp; Cui, Y. Y. &amp; Wang, S. B. &amp; Zou, J. X." pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="7980" refId="ref5048" refString="Gao, N., Cui, Y. Y., Wang, S. B. &amp; Zou, J. X. (2019) Two new species and the molecular phylogeography of the freshwater crab genus Bottapotamon (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Potamidae). PeerJ, 7, e 7980. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 7980" type="journal article" year="2019">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[1379,1437,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5); in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dai &amp; Ng" authorityYear="1994" box="[335,523,367,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Huananpotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[335,523,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Huananpotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pointed anteriorly or anteromedially, with the distal part of subterminal segment neck-shaped, terminal segment slender, inner margin with flap or projection, with small opening at pointed tip (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. Y." box="[151,257,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" refId="ref4907" refString="Dai, A. Y. (1999) Fauna Sinica: Arthropoda Crustacea Malacostraca Decapoda Parathelphusidae. Potamidae. Science Press, Beijing, xiii + 501 pp., 238 figs, 8 maps. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: pls. 63–73); and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[475,634,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Neilupotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,634,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Neilupotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, pointed anterolaterally, with the subterminal segment generally straight, terminal segment stout, inner margin almost straight to slightly convex, tip truncated with wide opening almost as wide as the terminal segment (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. Y." box="[534,642,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" refId="ref4907" refString="Dai, A. Y. (1999) Fauna Sinica: Arthropoda Crustacea Malacostraca Decapoda Parathelphusidae. Potamidae. Science Press, Beijing, xiii + 501 pp., 238 figs, 8 maps. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: pls. 201–204). 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang, 2022" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[823,983,511,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Jianghuaimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[823,983,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Jianghuaimon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[991,1096,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[991,1096,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can further be separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,310,547,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Bottapotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Bottapotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dai &amp; Ng" authorityYear="1994" box="[325,513,547,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Huananpotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,513,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Huananpotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turkay &amp; Dai" authorityYear="1997" box="[569,728,547,573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Neilupotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,728,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Neilupotamon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by differences in the carapace, male anterior thoracic sternites and male telson. See Table 1 for detailed comparisons. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang, 2022" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Xu &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[883,1043,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Jianghuaimon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[883,1043,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Jianghuaimon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1049,1154,583,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1049,1154,583,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was found to be syntopic with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dai &amp; Fan" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[207,488,619,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamidae" genus="Longpotamon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressum">
<emphasis box="[207,488,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Longpotamon depressum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can immediately be distinguished by its smaller size (CW &lt;
<quantity box="[1211,1290,618,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
) (versus CW &lt;
<quantity box="[175,256,654,681]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
in the latter), carapace anterolateral margin with 12–15 granules (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1097,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov., dorsal habitus. (A) male holotype SYSBM002003; (B) female paratype SYSBM002007." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (versus serrated, with 15–18 granules in the latter; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. Y." box="[396,503,691,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" refId="ref4907" refString="Dai, A. Y. (1999) Fauna Sinica: Arthropoda Crustacea Malacostraca Decapoda Parathelphusidae. Potamidae. Science Press, Beijing, xiii + 501 pp., 238 figs, 8 maps. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: pl. XXII fig. 2), granules on anterolateral margin low and inconspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1427,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[154,1434,181,1873]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Jianghuaimon dabiense gen. nov. et sp. nov., dorsal habitus. (A) male holotype SYSBM002003; (B) female paratype SYSBM002007." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899750/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) (versus relatively large conspicuous in the latter; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. Y." box="[696,803,727,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" refId="ref4907" refString="Dai, A. Y. (1999) Fauna Sinica: Arthropoda Crustacea Malacostraca Decapoda Parathelphusidae. Potamidae. Science Press, Beijing, xiii + 501 pp., 238 figs, 8 maps. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: pl. XXII fig. 2) and its G1 terminal segment large, stout, with rounded inner margin and wide opening at truncate tip (
<figureCitation box="[832,1019,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-21@6.[209,1378,181,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Jianghuaimon dabienese gen. nov. et sp. nov. (A–C, F–G, H–I) male holotype (20.4 × 15.7 mm), SYSBM002003; (D) male paratype (16.9 × 12.9 mm), NNU 20105JD1; (E) male paratype (17.5 × 13.2 mm), SYSBM002008; (A) right third maxilliped; (B) left G2, ventral view; (C–E) left G1s, ventral view; (F) major chela (right); (G) minor chela (left); (H) left G1 terminal segment, dorsal view; (I) left G1 terminal segment, ventral view. Scale bars: A–G = 2.0 mm; H–I = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899754/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Figs. 3C–E, H–I</figureCitation>
) (versus relatively small G1 terminal segment with bifurcated tip in the latter; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. Y." box="[608,715,799,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" refId="ref4907" refString="Dai, A. Y. (1999) Fauna Sinica: Arthropoda Crustacea Malacostraca Decapoda Parathelphusidae. Potamidae. Science Press, Beijing, xiii + 501 pp., 238 figs, 8 maps. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1999">Dai 1999</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 179).
</paragraph>
